interestingcomments.content: I currently have the Everyday 15" Messenger and it really good for the short hauls, house to car, road trips etc. Single sling not so good for extended carrying easily shifts, throwing one off balance. I have the 24-90 & 90-280 and can't wait for the 16-35 to complete the kit, should be able to include M240 hopefully and accessories. For that I am thinking the Everyday Backpack 30. Water-resistant for Vancouver and holding 15' laptop for going between our 2 places and road trips, photo trips and hiking to locations. Edited January 31, 2018 by MarkinVan
